sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Reporter of Invertase activity of Scre, pInv-rep-101SloxM1M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a reporter of invertase activity of Scre for Real-time measurement of dynamics of timing modules by SYSU-CHINA 2015.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pai Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This brick is constructed through cut-and-link of other bricks, without risky sources.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All reporter is constructed as following pattern: Constructive promoter :: RTS :: up-side-down RBS-mcherry-(ssra) :: RTS :: terminator

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Up-side-down RBS::mcherry-ssra with SloxM1, Scre recognition sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a special RBS::mcherry-ssra inverted into up-side-down form, with two SloxM1 sites at the upstream and downstream of the gene. SloxM1 can be recognized by invertase Scre and the middle mcherry can be restored through inversion. Ssra-tag in this sequence is moderately fast type (BBa_M0052) that accelerates the degradation but at a speed far less than expression.
This part can be used to construct the reporter for real-time invertase dynamics analysis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pai Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is constructed by PCR or cut-and-link of biobricks.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is up-side-down, hence can be inverted into normal sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
